1
00:00:55,458 --> 00:00:59,864
When people finish their day
and hurry home,

2
00:01:00,458 --> 00:01:02,210
my day starts.

3
00:01:19,666 --> 00:01:23,791
My diner is open from midnight
to 7:00 in the morning.

4
00:01:24,333 --> 00:01:27,375
They call it "Midnight Diner."

5
00:01:33,125 --> 00:01:34,541
Do I even have customers?

6
00:01:35,208 --> 00:01:37,041
More than you would expect.

7
00:01:39,559 --> 00:01:42,721
MIDNIGHT DINER: TOKYO STORIES

8
00:01:42,721 --> 00:01:47,398
PLUM RICE BALL

9
00:01:49,842 --> 00:01:52,482
The guy turned 60 and
switched jobs to be a care worker?

10
00:01:52,482 --> 00:01:53,333
That's right.

11
00:01:53,607 --> 00:01:55,960
He was a writer for a magazine,

12
00:01:55,960 --> 00:01:57,918
but he was no longer getting any work.

13
00:01:58,583 --> 00:02:01,031
Was he close to you?

14
00:02:01,031 --> 00:02:01,824
Yes.

15
00:02:02,192 --> 00:02:04,411
That guy used to offer me a lot of work.

16
00:02:06,956 --> 00:02:10,604
It's a tough job, by the way.

17
00:02:11,047 --> 00:02:12,672
Does he have the strength for it?

18
00:02:13,554 --> 00:02:17,387
His clients always tease,
"An old guy looking after an old guy."

19
00:02:18,016 --> 00:02:21,346
Here you go. The firefly squid
dressed with vinegar and miso,

20
00:02:21,346 --> 00:02:22,703
and the marinated squid.

21
00:02:25,059 --> 00:02:30,684
Spring has come. I just want to feel
peaceful while I'm alive.

22
00:02:32,522 --> 00:02:33,982
Another cold sake, please.

23
00:02:33,982 --> 00:02:34,940
Sure.

24
00:02:37,946 --> 00:02:41,779
Which glows more,
a firefly or a firefly squid?

25
00:02:42,377 --> 00:02:45,461
Firefly squid does.
Fireflies only glow around their buttocks.

26
00:02:46,783 --> 00:02:51,991
Either way,
they won't shine on our old days.

27
00:02:55,272 --> 00:02:56,813
It's delicious, isn't it?

28
00:02:58,084 --> 00:03:01,584
Honestly, I feel depressed when I think
about my days after retirement.

29
00:03:02,689 --> 00:03:04,814
You're already retired, aren't you?

30
00:03:08,542 --> 00:03:09,834
Hey, that's mine!

31
00:03:13,461 --> 00:03:17,118
Wouldn't it be better if you shaved
your hair and had a shining head?

32
00:03:17,118 --> 00:03:19,884
You should talk! You're hiding
your bald head with a cap!

33
00:03:19,884 --> 00:03:21,673
This is the fashion!

34
00:03:22,189 --> 00:03:23,231
À la mode.

35
00:03:23,886 --> 00:03:26,696
-Oh, dear.
-What is that...

36
00:03:26,696 --> 00:03:27,904
Welcome.

37
00:03:28,977 --> 00:03:32,352
Excuse me, I want to ask you something.

38
00:03:33,018 --> 00:03:37,614
Is Shinjuku New Art around here?

39
00:03:38,298 --> 00:03:40,714
It's right there,
but it's already closed by now.

40
00:03:41,258 --> 00:03:42,758
It closes at midnight.

41
00:03:43,366 --> 00:03:46,780
If you're looking to see the Virgin Mary,
you could visit the other one over there.

42
00:03:46,780 --> 00:03:48,797
Are you okay?

43
00:03:48,797 --> 00:03:50,111
Are you all right?

44
00:04:09,955 --> 00:04:12,580
We have both normal-sized
and small pickled plums,

45
00:04:12,855 --> 00:04:16,397
but he wanted the small ones.

46
00:04:17,783 --> 00:04:21,825
If you go to New Art before noon,
you can get an early-morning discount.

47
00:04:23,158 --> 00:04:24,366
Is that so?

48
00:04:26,926 --> 00:04:28,135
Can I have another one?

49
00:04:29,168 --> 00:04:30,168
Of course.

50
00:04:43,780 --> 00:04:46,530
I've heard of an old plum hag before,

51
00:04:47,196 --> 00:04:49,988
but never an old plum geezer.

52
00:04:52,336 --> 00:04:58,253
You found this at Yomogi town park, right?

53
00:04:59,023 --> 00:05:00,849
Who found this?

54
00:05:00,849 --> 00:05:01,916
-It was her.
-What?

55
00:05:01,916 --> 00:05:02,809
It was him, right?

56
00:05:02,809 --> 00:05:04,419
No, it was you!

57
00:05:04,419 --> 00:05:06,812
-No!
-Wait, wait.

58
00:05:06,812 --> 00:05:09,707
I need to talk to your parents,

59
00:05:09,707 --> 00:05:12,827
because the person who found this
has the right to receive a reward.

60
00:05:12,827 --> 00:05:13,680
-Yes!
-It was me!

61
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:15,113
Too close.

62
00:05:15,113 --> 00:05:17,220
Can we get some money?

63
00:05:17,220 --> 00:05:19,807
It depends.

64
00:05:20,095 --> 00:05:22,720
I'm not sure if it's cash.

65
00:05:23,866 --> 00:05:25,206
I gotta go now.

66
00:05:25,866 --> 00:05:28,033
-Me, too.
-Hey.

67
00:05:29,989 --> 00:05:32,618
Hey, wait!

68
00:05:32,618 --> 00:05:35,076
Oh, dear...

69
00:05:41,783 --> 00:05:45,359
You've got something between your teeth.

70
00:05:46,023 --> 00:05:47,999
Between your teeth.

71
00:05:48,425 --> 00:05:50,092
Something you ate.

72
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:54,490
No, no, no. How come she doesn't get it?

73
00:06:04,434 --> 00:06:05,434
Here you go.

74
00:06:06,175 --> 00:06:10,433
Mr. Umemiya taught Marilyn
bookkeeping at her high school.

75
00:06:10,433 --> 00:06:14,287
I see. He was her teacher
when she was a student.

76
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:16,541
Welcome.

77
00:06:17,070 --> 00:06:20,028
-Sorry to have kept you waiting.
-Marilyn. Come sit here.

78
00:06:20,803 --> 00:06:22,137
Thank you.

79
00:06:22,869 --> 00:06:25,258
Sensei, sorry for making you wait.

80
00:06:25,258 --> 00:06:27,633
No worries. I don't mind.

81
00:06:30,215 --> 00:06:33,256
-Master, another of these and the usual.
-Sure.

82
00:06:34,058 --> 00:06:37,100
I've been watching strip shows
for a long time,

83
00:06:37,849 --> 00:06:40,974
but today's was so special.
I'll never see anything like that again.

84
00:07:05,307 --> 00:07:07,598
A heavenly maiden!

85
00:07:09,443 --> 00:07:10,443
Marilyn!

86
00:07:41,007 --> 00:07:42,924
Unveiling!

87
00:07:44,057 --> 00:07:46,307
Student number nine!

88
00:07:48,123 --> 00:07:49,998
Mariko Kanno!

89
00:07:53,849 --> 00:07:55,058
Umejii?

90
00:07:56,836 --> 00:07:58,956
I was so surprised!

91
00:07:58,956 --> 00:08:01,563
I was called out to by my student number.

92
00:08:01,563 --> 00:08:03,896
It was like a sumo wrestler
entering the ring.

93
00:08:05,295 --> 00:08:08,110
I retired so long ago,

94
00:08:08,110 --> 00:08:10,705
but I couldn't help myself. I'm sorry.

95
00:08:11,265 --> 00:08:13,314
I'll call you that again next time, too.

96
00:08:13,314 --> 00:08:14,727
Stop it!

97
00:08:15,468 --> 00:08:16,760
Student number nine!

98
00:08:28,975 --> 00:08:29,975
Here you are.

99
00:08:31,543 --> 00:08:34,293
I started calling him Umejii.

100
00:08:36,464 --> 00:08:40,506
Since I was a slut like my mother,

101
00:08:40,506 --> 00:08:44,005
all my female classmates
disliked me and ignored me.

102
00:08:44,005 --> 00:08:46,386
-They were jealous.
-Maybe.

103
00:08:47,086 --> 00:08:49,652
But he was the only one
that wasn't like them.

104
00:08:49,652 --> 00:08:51,488
I'd call him by his nickname,
feeling close to him.

105
00:08:52,824 --> 00:08:56,761
At lunch time,
when I was smoking on the rooftop alone,

106
00:08:56,761 --> 00:08:59,303
you always gave me a rice ball with plum.

107
00:09:00,594 --> 00:09:04,178
You'd complain, saying you preferred
the one with cod roe.

108
00:09:04,178 --> 00:09:06,210
I didn't say that!

109
00:09:06,766 --> 00:09:10,433
You'd chop small pickled plums
and mix them with rice.

110
00:09:11,067 --> 00:09:13,067
It was delicious.

111
00:09:15,249 --> 00:09:16,983
How's your wife? Is she well?

112
00:09:17,471 --> 00:09:18,304
Yeah.

113
00:09:19,228 --> 00:09:22,020
She still makes me rice balls with these.

114
00:09:23,622 --> 00:09:26,080
Umejii, where are you gonna stay tonight?

115
00:09:30,291 --> 00:09:31,541
Tonight...

116
00:09:32,241 --> 00:09:34,116
It was great getting to see you,

117
00:09:34,796 --> 00:09:37,921
and I did see the Virgin Mary, too.
It was great.

118
00:09:39,056 --> 00:09:40,757
Don't be silly.

119
00:09:41,546 --> 00:09:44,535
Why don't you stay with me?
I live with my boyfriend, though.

120
00:09:45,007 --> 00:09:47,921
Good for you, Mr. Umemiya. I'm envious.

121
00:09:49,407 --> 00:09:50,865
Why not, then?

122
00:09:51,989 --> 00:09:53,073
Deal!

123
00:09:57,766 --> 00:10:00,766
Going with the flow

124
00:10:01,993 --> 00:10:05,659
That night, he stayed at Marilyn's.

125
00:10:06,221 --> 00:10:11,721
The next day, they went to Tokyo Skytree
since Marilyn had the day off.

126
00:10:12,415 --> 00:10:15,874
Our friends

127
00:10:18,475 --> 00:10:20,183
Forever

128
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:23,566
Support each other forever

129
00:10:23,566 --> 00:10:25,965
Forever

130
00:10:34,769 --> 00:10:36,144
Yes, there.

131
00:10:37,239 --> 00:10:38,280
Kibi...

132
00:10:46,933 --> 00:10:52,117
After that, Umejii wanted
to buy a scarf for his wife,

133
00:10:52,117 --> 00:10:55,873
so he bought one at a department store
in Ueno, and I took him to the station.

134
00:10:55,873 --> 00:10:56,957
I see.

135
00:10:58,262 --> 00:10:59,554
Welcome.

136
00:11:03,909 --> 00:11:06,242
Umejii! What're you doing here?

137
00:11:09,248 --> 00:11:11,498
Student number nine!

138
00:11:13,089 --> 00:11:14,631
Mariko Kanno!

139
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:17,058
Long time no see!

140
00:11:18,841 --> 00:11:20,355
Have a seat.

141
00:11:21,056 --> 00:11:25,473
He was standing in front of the theater,
staring at her poster.

142
00:11:26,141 --> 00:11:27,850
He doesn't remember me, either.

143
00:11:28,930 --> 00:11:30,359
In that case...

144
00:11:30,359 --> 00:11:31,837
It can't be helped.

145
00:11:31,837 --> 00:11:34,621
He's old enough to be like that.

146
00:11:35,809 --> 00:11:40,635
Your big photo was hanging on the wall.

147
00:11:41,357 --> 00:11:46,691
I was so happy to see you
hard at work in Tokyo.

148
00:11:48,137 --> 00:11:50,964
Umejii, aren't you hungry?

149
00:11:51,859 --> 00:11:52,859
Yeah.

150
00:11:53,637 --> 00:11:55,387
I am.

151
00:11:56,283 --> 00:12:01,908
I came up here from Fukushima today,
and I haven't eaten anything.

152
00:12:02,439 --> 00:12:06,025
Master, can I have a rice ball
with the little pickled plums?

153
00:12:06,025 --> 00:12:09,413
And another one with cod roe, please.

154
00:12:09,413 --> 00:12:10,667
She likes that one.

155
00:12:11,401 --> 00:12:12,401
Of course.

156
00:12:16,430 --> 00:12:19,888
You were always complaining.

157
00:12:21,759 --> 00:12:23,634
I always was, wasn't I?

158
00:12:26,430 --> 00:12:29,014
What's wrong? You look sad.

159
00:12:31,704 --> 00:12:36,890
When she told me she'd give up high school
to be a dancer,

160
00:12:37,378 --> 00:12:41,176
I tried so hard to stop her,
but she wouldn't listen to me at all.

161
00:12:41,566 --> 00:12:44,316
She's so stubborn. Isn't that right?

162
00:13:18,750 --> 00:13:20,136
Here you go.

163
00:13:22,428 --> 00:13:25,905
Do you cook at home, too?

164
00:13:26,724 --> 00:13:30,057
I just go home and go to sleep.

165
00:13:30,816 --> 00:13:33,965
You should cook her meals sometimes.

166
00:13:34,432 --> 00:13:35,892
I bet she'd be pleased.

167
00:13:35,892 --> 00:13:37,179
Umejii, Master is--

168
00:13:37,179 --> 00:13:41,067
You're right.
I should spoil her sometimes.

169
00:13:41,669 --> 00:13:46,166
If you're not nice at home,
she'll leave you.

170
00:13:46,932 --> 00:13:48,057
I'll try my best.

171
00:13:49,584 --> 00:13:54,543
That night, Marilyn took Mr. Umemiya
to her home again.

172
00:13:55,483 --> 00:14:01,819
The next day, although she asked him
his home phone number and address,

173
00:14:01,819 --> 00:14:05,278
he wouldn't tell her, changing the subject
and talking about old times instead.

174
00:14:22,431 --> 00:14:25,931
I feel sorry for the pickled plum.

175
00:14:26,737 --> 00:14:30,112
But if I don't crush it,
I can't get its juice.

176
00:14:31,577 --> 00:14:33,577
I prefer these ones.

177
00:14:37,288 --> 00:14:40,454
They taste good with a generous amount
of salt, don't they?

178
00:14:41,008 --> 00:14:42,008
Yes.

179
00:14:42,591 --> 00:14:48,011
My wife's pickles
aren't quite so salty these days.

180
00:14:48,436 --> 00:14:50,561
She must care about your health.

181
00:14:51,258 --> 00:14:53,133
If you consume too much salt...

182
00:14:53,774 --> 00:14:55,524
Can I see your hand, please?

183
00:14:56,545 --> 00:14:58,465
This here is the kidney's pressure point.

184
00:14:58,465 --> 00:15:02,388
And right here is the adrenal gland's.
I'm gonna press here.

185
00:15:03,162 --> 00:15:04,579
Do you feel anything?

186
00:15:04,579 --> 00:15:05,892
Hey, you!

187
00:15:06,581 --> 00:15:10,275
You're going to open your own
chiropractic clinic, aren't you?

188
00:15:10,275 --> 00:15:13,900
If you reveal your trick so easily,
your business will fail right away.

189
00:15:14,454 --> 00:15:17,178
-Yes.
-I'm sorry for the trouble.

190
00:15:17,178 --> 00:15:18,849
It felt good, anyway.

191
00:15:21,822 --> 00:15:23,072
Sorry, Kibi.

192
00:15:24,235 --> 00:15:26,610
Here's the scarf!

193
00:15:27,291 --> 00:15:29,405
Don't forget this.

194
00:15:29,405 --> 00:15:31,592
You'll give it to your wife, won't you?

195
00:15:32,341 --> 00:15:35,559
You don't need to do that.

196
00:15:35,559 --> 00:15:36,778
You have it, Mariko.

197
00:15:37,256 --> 00:15:39,389
Don't be silly.

198
00:15:39,389 --> 00:15:44,813
You asked me to pick out a nice one.
We bought this together in Ueno!

199
00:15:44,813 --> 00:15:45,896
Here.

200
00:15:46,922 --> 00:15:48,047
Really?

201
00:15:50,466 --> 00:15:53,175
I'm so old and absentminded nowadays.

202
00:15:53,883 --> 00:15:55,840
Thank you. I'll take this to her.

203
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:56,923
Marilyn.

204
00:15:58,593 --> 00:16:00,838
Have you managed to talk to his family?

205
00:16:00,838 --> 00:16:04,278
I called the high school,
but they didn't know his contacts' info.

206
00:16:04,864 --> 00:16:08,238
And I cut ties with people there.

207
00:16:08,949 --> 00:16:10,157
I see.

208
00:16:12,227 --> 00:16:15,936
Good evening. Is Mr. Umemiya here?

209
00:16:17,946 --> 00:16:19,415
Dad!

210
00:16:20,756 --> 00:16:23,111
We were looking all over for you!

211
00:16:23,111 --> 00:16:26,498
Mr. Umemiya lost this cell phone.

212
00:16:26,498 --> 00:16:31,493
His daughters tried to track it by GPS,
but it had run out of battery.

213
00:16:32,008 --> 00:16:36,631
My sister and I take turns
looking after him,

214
00:16:37,351 --> 00:16:41,099
but I've been busy the last few days.

215
00:16:41,099 --> 00:16:44,766
We both thought
he was with the other sister.

216
00:16:46,306 --> 00:16:50,431
We are very sorry for the trouble.

217
00:16:52,030 --> 00:16:55,447
Since our mother passed away
two months ago...

218
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:59,820
he's suddenly gone strange.

219
00:17:01,882 --> 00:17:03,913
Why are you crying?

220
00:17:03,913 --> 00:17:05,800
Dad!

221
00:17:11,258 --> 00:17:12,951
You, Midori!

222
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:16,114
Long time no see...

223
00:17:16,114 --> 00:17:17,756
Slut Mariko.

224
00:17:18,422 --> 00:17:25,715
This woman, Midori, works for the
care facility Mr. Umemiya goes to.

225
00:17:25,715 --> 00:17:31,169
In high school, she was the leader
of a group that ignored Marilyn.

226
00:17:31,669 --> 00:17:32,794
Thank you.

227
00:17:34,390 --> 00:17:37,515
Please come to the police station with me
to fill out several documents.

228
00:17:37,515 --> 00:17:39,754
Sure. Thank you.

229
00:17:39,754 --> 00:17:43,379
Dad, please watch your step.

230
00:17:44,072 --> 00:17:47,484
-What a relief to have found him!
-Such a relief.

231
00:18:10,856 --> 00:18:12,356
Umemiya sensei...

232
00:18:13,303 --> 00:18:19,178
There are times when he's fine,
but he occasionally loses his memory.

233
00:18:24,928 --> 00:18:28,637
I heard his cell phone ran out of battery.

234
00:18:30,164 --> 00:18:32,789
How come you knew he was in Tokyo, then?

235
00:18:35,916 --> 00:18:39,208
He visits our facility once a week.

236
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:43,000
On the day he went missing...

237
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:47,323
he left this behind.

238
00:18:47,323 --> 00:18:50,890
MARILYN - I FOUND THE RIGHT PLACE
IT'S MY IDEAL JOB

239
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,000
Gosh...

240
00:18:54,833 --> 00:18:58,341
It's an article from when
I first went onstage at New Art.

241
00:18:58,682 --> 00:19:01,657
Every time he'd visit, he'd always say,

242
00:19:02,343 --> 00:19:05,718
"I thought I should've have taken
Mariko back home from Tokyo,

243
00:19:06,593 --> 00:19:10,029
but Mariko has found her place at last.

244
00:19:10,816 --> 00:19:14,941
I won't try to stop her, because she said
in the interview that it's her ideal job."

245
00:19:16,942 --> 00:19:18,314
Umejii...

246
00:19:20,792 --> 00:19:23,461
I hated that nickname.

247
00:19:25,961 --> 00:19:29,492
I hated you as well, how you'd behave
as if you were the only special student.

248
00:19:30,415 --> 00:19:34,803
I hated you, too,
always with those other girls.

249
00:19:36,884 --> 00:19:41,134
I spent more time with him than you,

250
00:19:41,910 --> 00:19:45,679
but he'd always cared most about you.

251
00:19:46,365 --> 00:19:48,324
He carried it with him all the time.

252
00:19:50,576 --> 00:19:54,790
He never gave me a rice ball
with little pickled plums,

253
00:19:55,289 --> 00:19:57,570
back in high school or now.

254
00:20:04,171 --> 00:20:05,379
Wait a second.

255
00:20:06,781 --> 00:20:10,448
Are you leaving without eating anything?

256
00:20:13,365 --> 00:20:16,031
Master, a rice ball
with little pickled plums, please.

257
00:20:17,069 --> 00:20:19,111
-Here you go.
-What?

258
00:20:21,374 --> 00:20:22,832
The other one is on me.

259
00:20:23,869 --> 00:20:24,827
Are you sure?

260
00:20:36,981 --> 00:20:40,106
If you don't eat it, I will.

261
00:21:28,497 --> 00:21:33,967
Since then, Marilyn takes my rice balls
with the little pickled plums with her

262
00:21:34,575 --> 00:21:37,325
to bring to Mr. Umemiya from time to time.

263
00:21:38,116 --> 00:21:41,599
Hana. What did you make?

264
00:21:41,599 --> 00:21:42,724
It's a hydrangea.

265
00:21:42,724 --> 00:21:44,706
A hydrangea!

266
00:21:44,706 --> 00:21:46,289
What is yours?

267
00:21:46,825 --> 00:21:48,907
A photograph of...

268
00:22:02,849 --> 00:22:05,502
Remove the pits from the pickled plums,
chop them into bits,

269
00:22:05,502 --> 00:22:07,836
and mix them in
with rice and sesame seeds.

270
00:22:08,568 --> 00:22:10,288
Nori has two sides.

271
00:22:10,288 --> 00:22:12,368
The shiny side is the head.

272
00:22:12,368 --> 00:22:16,786
Putting the head facing out feels nicer
on your lips and tastes better, too.

273
00:22:17,626 --> 00:22:19,215
Here you go.

274
00:22:26,477 --> 00:22:27,852
Wonderful.

275
00:22:29,441 --> 00:22:30,897
Good night!

276
00:22:30,897 --> 00:22:31,897
Night.

277
00:23:42,420 --> 00:23:47,400
THIS STORY IS A WORK OF FICTION

